 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality would like to advise the residents and businesses that there has been an unforseen delay in the repair of the water pipeline to Uitenhage. "At this stage, it is difficult to predict when water will be restored," said Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality Communications Officer, Mthubanzi Mniki. "Water tankers will continue to be deployed in affected areas." Mniki said that the affected areas include: "One of the main water supply pipelines supplying Uitenhage burst," he added. "This has caused reservoirs to empty and large parts of Uitenhage are either without water or experiencing low pressure. "The pipeline has been shutdown and repair work is continuing." Miniki said that at this stage, water tankers have been deployed at the following locations: "Residents are urged to use water sparingly." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 